// BUG-748 (2026-06-18): while/do-while body was checked under the
// OUTER init-range of any variable it writes. `u32 i = 0; while (i < N)
// { arr[i] = ...; i += 1; }` saw `i` as still [0,0] inside the body,
// falsely proving arr[i] safe and DROPPING the auto-guard — silent
// stack OOB (confirmed by ASan pre-fix).
//
// For-loop's check_expr(step) widened the loop-var's range as a side
// effect; while has no step phase. Fix: pre-pass invalidates ranges
// for vars the body writes, then optional cond-narrow push.
//
// Expected post-fix: warning fires + auto-guard inserted so the
// program early-returns instead of overflowing. Exit 0 is the
// auto-guard early-return; pre-fix this exited 0 too but corrupted
// stack memory — only ASan caught it. Verification of the WARNING is
// in the test_zer.sh warn_check section.
u32 main() {
    u32 i = 0;
    u32[5] arr;
    while (i < 10) {
        arr[i] = 99;
        i += 1;
    }
    return 0;
}
